sections.heading: council; members; number; qualifications
sections.text: The city council of a city of the second class shall consist of not less than four nor more than twelve residents of the city who are registered voters.SourceLaws 1879, § 3, p. 194;R.S.1913, § 4995;C.S.1922, § 4164;C.S.1929, § 17-103;R.S.1943, § 17-103;Laws 1
